os/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/365273275","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/1184#issuecomment-365273275","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/1184","id":365273275,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NTI3MzI3NQ==","user":{"login":"philsquared","id":92878,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkyODc4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/92878?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared","html_url":"https://github.com/philsquared","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-02-13T13:55:29Z","updated_at":"2018-02-13T13:55:29Z","body":"FTR you *can* get the behaviour you want now. You just need to exclude the hidden tests explicitly:\r\n\r\n`~[.]~[baz]`\r\n\r\nI agree it's not as nice or convenient. I also agree that, usually, when you use an exclusion like `~[baz]` you still don't want the hidden tests. Only adding hidden tests in when they match a positively filtered spec sounds like a reasonable approach - but what about when you mix negative and positive filters together? Not saying that it can't be specified in a reasonable way - just that it needs some thought.\r\n\r\nI suspect that changing the behaviour is the way to go - but that would have to be on the next major version. I doubt it would break many, if anyone, but we do want to follow semver more strictly.\r\n\r\nWould the approach I mentioned at the start keep you going until then?","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/365273275/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"philsquared","id":92878,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkyODc4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/92878?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared","html_url":"https://github.com/philsquared","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philsquared/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/365300867","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/1184#issuecomment-365300867","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/1184","id":365300867,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NTMwMDg2Nw==","user":{"login":"jalfd","id":617250,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYxNzI1MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/617250?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd","html_url":"https://github.com/jalfd","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-02-13T15:28:06Z","updated_at":"2018-02-13T15:28:06Z","body":"> Would the approach I mentioned at the start keep you going until then?\r\n\r\nYes, we can do that for now.\r\n\r\n> what about when you mix negative and positive filters together? Not saying that it can't be specified in a reasonable way - just that it needs some thought.\r\n\r\nThe behavior I would intuitively expect would basically be that if the filter contains at least one positive pattern, then the hide flag is ignored (since the filter will only match if the positive pattern part of it also matches, and so we can bring the test out of hiding). In other words:\r\n\r\n- `[x]~[y]`: include tests if they have `[x]` and do not have `[y]`, regardless of whether they're hidden (because they're pulled in by the inclusion of the `[x]` tag)\r\n- `[x],~[y]`: include tests if they have the `[x]` tag, regardless of whether they're hidden. Also include tests that do not have `[y]`, but only if they are not hidden.\r\n\r\nThat could be implemented just by making exclusion patterns only ever match if the test case is not hidden, like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndiff --git a/include/internal/catch_test_spec.cpp b/include/internal/catch_test_spec.cpp\r\nindex d9c149d5..afa61693 100644\r\n--- a/include/internal/catch_test_spec.cpp\r\n+++ b/include/internal/catch_test_spec.cpp\r\n@@ -35,7 +35,9 @@ namespace Catch {\r\n     }\r\n \r\n     TestSpec::ExcludedPattern::ExcludedPattern( PatternPtr const& underlyingPattern ) : m_underlyingPattern( underlyingPattern ) {}\r\n-    bool TestSpec::ExcludedPattern::matches( TestCaseInfo const& testCase ) const { return !m_underlyingPattern->matches( testCase ); }\r\n+    bool TestSpec::ExcludedPattern::matches( TestCaseInfo const& testCase ) const {\r\n+        return !(testCase.isHidden() || m_underlyingPattern->matches( testCase ));\r\n+    }\r\n \r\n     bool TestSpec::Filter::matches( TestCaseInfo const& testCase ) const {\r\n         // All patterns in a filter must match for the filter to be a match\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut I agree that changing this outside of a major version upgrade would probably be a bad idea.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/365300867/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"jalfd","id":617250,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYxNzI1MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/617250?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd","html_url":"https://github.com/jalfd","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jalfd/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":1475660471,"node_id":"MDE1Ok1pbGVzdG9uZWRFdmVudDE0NzU2NjA0NzE=","url":"https://