r\n```\r\nthen all tests except `sometest` are correctly run, but the benchmarks are *also* incorrectly run.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nSince the benchmarks are not run when `./test` is run, they should also not be run when `./test exclude:sometest` is run.\r\n\r\n**Reproduction steps**\r\nA MWE (`test.cpp`):\r\n\r\n```C++\r\n#define CATCH_CONFIG_ENABLE_BENCHMARKING\r\n#include \"catch.hpp\"\r\n\r\nTEST_CASE( \"a\", \"[mytests]\") {\r\n    REQUIRE( true );\r\n}\r\n\r\nTEST_CASE( b\", \"[mytests]\") {\r\n    REQUIRE( true );\r\n}\r\n\r\nTEST_CASE( c\", \"[!benchmark]\") {\r\n    \r\n    BENCHMARK( \"mybenchmark\" ) {\r\n\r\n        int s=0;\r\n        for (int i=0; i<10; i++)\r\n            s++;\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n```\r\nCompile with \r\n```bash\r\ng++ -std=c++14 -c test.cpp -o test\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen `./test` is run, only tests `a` and `b` run (correct behaviour).\r\nWhen `./test except:a` is run, `b` runs (correctly), but `c` incorrectly also runs.\r\n\r\n**Platform information:**\r\n - OS: Ubuntu 18\r\n - Compiler+version: **GCC v8.3.0**\r\n - Catch version: **v2.10.0**\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/1829/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/1829/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":3887059230,"node_id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50Mzg4NzA1OTIzMA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/events/3887059230","actor":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"